  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Please, could you add the possibility to check called methods as in `ethereum-waffle` package with and without arguments?\r\n\r\nI suppose it will be handy to test some logic that should be executed right after contract deployment or to have more variety when users will test contract functions.\r\n\r\nExample from `ethereum-waffle` docs:\r\n```typescript\r\n// Testing if function was called on the provided contract\r\nawait token.balanceOf(wallet.address)\r\nexpect('balanceOf').to.be.calledOnContract(token);\r\n\r\n// Testing if function with certain arguments was called on provided contract\r\nawait token.balanceOf(wallet.address)\r\nexpect('balanceOf').to.be.calledOnContractWith(token, [wallet.address]);\r\n```",
  "closed_by": null,
